2026-07-21T17:00:00Z,"One simple tip every renter should know: take photos before you move in.
Moving into a new place is exciting, but don’t let the excitement make you skip the little things. Before you unpack your boxes, take a few minutes to walk through the home and document the condition of everything.
Take pictures of walls, floors, appliances, cabinets, bathrooms, and anything that already has damage or wear. Even small things like a scratch on the floor or a mark on the wall can be easy to forget months later.
Having those photos gives you peace of mind and helps avoid misunderstandings when it’s time to move out. It’s a simple habit that can save you time, stress, and possibly money.
A good rental experience starts with good communication and keeping records. Protect yourself, take care of your home, and make your space feel like your own.
Small steps today can make moving day much easier.
